If you want a cleaner ranking, I’d strongly recommend:
	1.	use canonical grouping
	2.	prefer full names plus common aliases
	3.	avoid very short ambiguous aliases unless necessary

You can also ask a different question: not “how many segments mention them?” but “how many total name mentions?” That’s a different metric.

For that, use this pattern:

WITH name_map(person, alias) AS (
  VALUES
    ('Donald Trump', 'Trump'),
    ('Donald Trump', 'Donald Trump'),
    ('Joe Biden', 'Biden'),
    ('Joe Biden', 'Joe Biden'),
    ('Elon Musk', 'Musk'),
    ('Elon Musk', 'Elon Musk')
),
hits AS (
  SELECT
    person,
    SUM(
      (length(lower(text)) - length(replace(lower(text), lower(alias), '')))
      / length(alias)
    ) AS mention_count
  FROM name_map
  JOIN segments
    ON lower(text) LIKE '%' || lower(alias) || '%'
  GROUP BY person, alias
)
SELECT
  person,
  SUM(mention_count) AS total_mentions
FROM hits
GROUP BY person
ORDER BY total_mentions DESC, person;
